"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"[![James Surowiecki](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/1\\\\*AFr0-PlJn8Zvd6uvbNDLSg.jpeg)](https://surowiecki.medium.com/?source=post_page-----9d2b28177a86-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://surowiecki.medium.com/?source=post_page-----9d2b28177a86-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[James Surowiecki](https://surowiecki.medium.com/?source=post_page-----9d2b28177a86-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://surowiecki.medium.com/dont-blame-capitalism-for-the-lack-of-covid-tests-blame-the-fda-9d2b28177a86?source=post_page-----9d2b28177a86-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[5 days ago·4 min read](https://surowiecki.medium.com/dont-blame-capitalism-for-the-lack-of-covid-tests-blame-the-fda-9d2b28177a86?source=post_page-----9d2b28177a86-----------------------------------)\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1280/1\\\\*q_nY00HkZe_Kt2rztNfhYg.jpeg)\\n\\nFae for Creative Commons\\n\\nBy now, just about everyone recognizes that the shortages and the high prices of rapid at-home antigen tests, which I wrote about yesterday, is a problem. But one common mistake that people are making is to blame those shortages, and especially those high prices, on “capitalism.” If it weren’t for greedy capitalists, the argument implicitly (and explicitly) goes, tests would…\\n\",\"timestamp\":1641435358,\"title\":\"Don’t Blame Capitalism for the Lack of Covid Tests. Blame the FDA.\"},\"digest\":\"PHp--JchBGTErOHrfPMFzmGGk_uwRMCpicTCNanSxrk\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xBFE7a4A2dDF45f0fF98adF02e21Bf5a0a222dA7B\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"Gu7Xmy7k3G3s1j1NUva4m15vP3bqzvP6hvBGqw_S8XY\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"E3ekYSjWjnb09hgO9o6x1MqbEP5m0vYj38tmgsq7dWY\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"TPzKRjwSzeIJ-ZBnXvRv878fQIsJN-otRaQdJQNozh1yJjF1SOeGBLIHdRxEAreDKH6-Mv14YrUuOCHiF_utLw\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x429bd128a98120b4b952d15bf780cb2a6f54b